Subject: [PATCH] =?UTF-8?q?feat:=20teacher-car=20stickiness=20=E2=80=94=20?=
 =?UTF-8?q?keep=20teachers=20on=20the=20same=20car=20all=20day?=
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Eliminates wasteful branch-return trips when a teacher bounces between
multiple cars in a single day. Once a teacher is placed on a car for a
given day, their subsequent students get a strong routing preference for
that same car.

- teacherCarAffinity map tracks teacher→car per day, primed from manual placements
- candidateFor sort adds stickyBonus (same car) / stickyPenalty (different car)
- Affinity recorded for drops, double-drops (sibling teacher), and group slots
- New setting: stickyBonusKm (default 15) — configurable in Settings modal
- 0 = off, higher = stronger preference to keep teacher on same car

Analysis of live data showed 13 multi-car teacher-day cases causing
~468 min/day of wasted branch-return idle time. This change chains
sessions so teachers go student→student without returning to branch.
